(399, 'travelling_salesman_problem.png', 'Travelling Salesman Problem', 'What&#39;s the complexity class of the best linear programming cutting-plane techniques?  I couldn&#39;t find it anywhere.  Man, the Garfield guy doesn&#39;t have these problems ...'),
(400, 'important_life_lesson.png', 'Important Life Lesson', 'I didn&#39;t even know I *had* the Monty Python &#39;Lumberjack&#39; song.'),
(401, 'large_hadron_collider.png', 'Large Hadron Collider', 'When charged particles of more than 5 TeV pass through a bubble chamber, they leave a trail of candy.'),
(402, '1000_miles_north.png', '1,000 Miles North', 'Twister would&#39;ve been a much better movie if they&#39;d cut out the bad-guy storm chaser and all the emotional romance crap.  All you need for a good movie are tornados and scientists.  Actually, that&#39;s all you need for anything.'),
(403, 'convincing_pickup_line.png', 'Convincing Pickup Line', 'Check it out; I&#39;ve had sex with someone who&#39;s had sex with someone who&#39;s written a paper with Paul ErdÅ‘s!'),
(404, '', '', ''),
(405, 'journal_3.png', 'Journal 3', 'Oh, and, uh, if the Russian government asks, that submarine was always there.'),
(406, 'venting.png', 'Venting', 'P.P.S. I can kill you with my brain.');
INSERT INTO `comix` (`id`, `picid`, `title`, `alttext`) VALUES
(407, 'cheap_gps.png', 'Cheap GPS', 'In lieu of mapping software, I once wrote a Perl program which, given a USB GPS receiver and a destination, printed &#39;LEFT&#39; &#39;RIGHT&#39; OR &#39;STRAIGHT&#39; based on my heading.'),
(408, 'overqualified.png', 'Overqualified', 'To anyone I&#39;ve taken on a terrible date, this is retroactively my cover story.'),
(409, 'electric_skateboard_double_comic.png', 'Electric Skateboard (Double Comic)', 'Unsafe vehicles, hills, and philosophy go hand in hand.'),
(410, 'math_paper.png', 'Math Paper', 'That&#39;s nothing.  I once lost my genetics, rocketry, and stripping licenses in a single incident.'),
(411, 'techno.png', 'Techno', 'I don&#39;t know what&#39;s worse -- that there exists broken-hard-drive-sound techno, or that it&#39;s not half bad.'),
(412, 'startled.png', 'Startled', '...'),
(413, 'new_pet.png', 'New Pet', 'ONE LAPTOP PER HAMSTER!'),
(414, 'mistranslations.png', 'Mistranslations', 'Oh, I think this word might mean &#39;Crisco&#39;!'),
(415, 'restraining_order.png', 'Restraining Order', 'On Mondays I go running, so you&#39;ll have to get up early and follow along on a parallel street.  What fun!'),
(416, 'zealous_autoconfig.png', 'Zealous Autoconfig', 'I hear this is an option in the latest Ubuntu release.'),
(417, 'the_man_who_fell_sideways.png', 'The Man Who Fell Sideways', 'Strip originally conceived in conversation with Jeph Jacques.  Soon to be a major motion picture.'),
(418, 'stove_ownership.png', 'Stove Ownership', 'Although maybe it&#39;s just a phase, like freshman year of college when I realized I could just buy frosting in a can.'),
(419, 'forks_and_spoons.png', 'Forks and Spoons', 'Their biggest mistake was bringing Rachael Ray and Emeril to tour the lab and sign off on the project.  That&#39;s when Spielberg caught wind of it.'),
(420, 'jealousy.png', 'Jealousy', 'Oh, huh, so you didn&#39;t know that story?'),
(421, 'making_hash_browns.png', 'Making Hash Browns', 'There are at least fourteen ways this could go badly (seventeen if that fork is a dangerous crossbreed.)'),
(422, 'a_better_idea.png', 'A Better Idea', 'It&#39;s *almost* enough to make me want to redo high school.'),
(423, 'finish_line.png', 'Finish Line', 'The question with Lucy and the football was always whether, on some level, she believed the things she said.'),
(424, 'security_holes.png', 'Security Holes', 'True story: I had to try several times to upload this comic because my ssh key was blacklisted.'),
(425, 'fortune_cookies.png', 'Fortune Cookies', '&#39;You will have hot, steamy, sweaty sex ... IN BED!&#39;'),
(426, 'geohashing.png', 'Geohashing', 'Saturday is game night.'),
(427, 'bad_timing.png', 'Bad Timing', 'Protip: Even without the red spiders, never have that conversation halfway through a balloon ride.'),
(428, 'starwatching.png', 'Starwatching', 'I always figured the word &#39;blog&#39; would sound *less* silly as the years went by.'),
(429, 'fantasy.png', 'Fantasy', 'I guess if she accepted irrational realities, she&#39;d hardly be my fantasy.'),
(430, 'every_damn_morning.png', 'Every Damn Morning', 'There was something about a cup and a sword and a tree and a green hill ...'),
(431, 'delivery.png', 'Delivery', 'Ma&#39;am, I admit that wasn&#39;t in the best taste, but you have to admire my delivery!  Ha ha, get it?  Oh God, don&#39;t throw those syringes!  Your baby&#39;s fine!'),
(432, 'journal_4.png', 'Journal 4', 'Man, this emo shit was supposed to be for people who didn&#39;t have hats.'),
(433, 'journal_5.png', 'Journal 5', '&#39;Pick you up at eight?&#39; &#39;Nine.  I&#39;ve got to re-mine the driveway.&#39;'),
(434, 'xkcd_goes_to_the_airport.png', 'xkcd Goes to the Airport', 'Under three ounces, but it stains panties.'),
(435, 'purity.png', 'Purity', 'On the other hand, physicists like to say physics is to math as sex is to masturbation.'),
(436, 'how_it_happened.png', 'How it Happened', 'I was there, dude.'),
(437, 'suv.png', 'SUV', 'Electric skateboards, by cost, get the equivalent of about 300 miles per gallon.  Lithium batteries just need to get cheaper.'),
(438, 'internet_argument.png', 'Internet Argument', 'It&#39;s easier to be an asshole to words than to people.'),
(439, 'thinking_ahead.png', 'Thinking Ahead', 'Did he just go crazy and jump out the window?'),
(440, 'road_rage.png', 'Road Rage', 'Okay, now just as the loss hits him, slam on the brakes.'),
(441, 'babies.png', 'Babies', 'I bet my future kids will read this someday.  DEAR FUTURE KIDS: how did you get internet in the cellar?'),
(442, 'xkcd_loves_the_discovery_channel.png', 'xkcd Loves the Discovery Channel', 'I love the title-text!'),
(443, 'know_your_vines.png', 'Know Your Vines', 'Friggin&#39; modern tents don&#39;t have a single piece of rope.'),
(444, 'macgyver_gets_lazy.png', 'Macgyver Gets Lazy', 'At the time of this writing, Wikipedia has a wonderful article titled &#39;List of problems solved by Macgyver&#39;.'),
(445, 'i_am_not_good_with_boomerangs.png', 'I Am Not Good with Boomerangs', 'Bonus strip: just read the rightmost panels straight down. '),
(446, 'in_popular_culture.png', 'In Popular Culture', 'Someday the &#39;in popular culture&#39; section will have its own article with an &#39;in popular culture&#39; section.  It will reference this title-text referencing it, and the blogosphere will implode.'),
(447, 'too_old_for_this_shit.png', 'Too Old For This Shit', 'They say if a mathematician doesn&#39;t do their great work by age eleven, they never will.'),
(448, 'good_morning.png', 'Good Morning', 'As my standard, I use going to sleep at midnight and waking up at 8 AM.'),
(449, 'things_fall_apart.png', 'Things Fall Apart', '&#39;I&#39;m nothing without you&#39; is a fucked-up sentiment.'),
(450, 'the_sea.png', 'The Sea', 'And then a second one, to drain the sea.'),
(451, 'impostor.png', 'Impostor', 'If you think this is too hard on literary criticism, read the Wikipedia article on deconstruction.'),
(452, 'mission.png', 'Mission', 'Don&#39;t you know?  The chances of a random object being a scone are about one in six.'),
(453, 'upcoming_hurricanes.png', 'Upcoming Hurricanes', 'I&#39;d like to see more damage assessments for hurricanes hitting New York and flooding Manhattan -- something like the 1938 Long Island Express, but aimed a bit more to the west.  It&#39;s just a matter of time.'),
(454, 'rewiring.png', 'Rewiring', 'My friend Elizabeth tried to mail one end of the cable to me and thread the mail system.'),
(455, 'hats.png', 'Hats', '...'),
(456, 'cautionary.png', 'Cautionary', 'This really is a true story, and she doesn&#39;t know I put it in my comic because her wifi hasn&#39;t worked for weeks.'),
(457, 'frustration.png', 'Frustration', '&#39;Don&#39;t worry, I can do it in under a minute.&#39; &#39;Yes, I&#39;ve noticed.&#39;'),
(458, 'regrets.png', 'Regrets', 'And nothing for &#39;I&#39;m glad I saw Epic Movie.&#39;'),
(459, 'holy_ghost.png', 'Holy Ghost', 'Okay, everyone, cross yourselves, then cross the streams.'),
(460, 'paleontology.png', 'Paleontology', 'Dinosaurs totally jumped the ichthyosaur when they got rid of Brontosaurus.'),
(461, 'google_maps.png', 'Google Maps', 'Apparently Google assumes you&#39;re traveling during the ferry&#39;s normal operating hours.  We lost two hours circling that damn lake (to say nothing of the Straw Man).'),
(462, 'freemanic_paracusia.png', 'Freemanic Paracusia', 'It&#39;s amazing what it does for YouTube comments.'),
(463, 'voting_machines.png', 'Voting Machines', 'And that&#39;s *another* crypto conference I&#39;ve been kicked out of.  C&#39;mon, it&#39;s a great analogy!'),
(464, 'rba.png', 'RBA', 'This is a story all about how I started drinking.'),
(465, 'quantum_teleportation.png', 'Quantum Teleportation', 'Science should be exactly as cool as the headlines sound.  Like the &#39;RUSSIANS CUT APART AND REASSEMBLE DOGS&#39; thing.'),
(466, 'moving.png', 'Moving', 'We need a special holiday to honor the countless kind souls with unsecured networks named &#39;linksys&#39;.'),
(467, 'x_girls_y_cups.png', 'X Girls Y Cups', 'Also no results: 1girl10000cups, 2girls(5+3i)cups, 65536girls65536cups, or 3frenchhens2turtledoves1cup.'),
(468, 'fetishes.png', 'Fetishes', 'They eventually resolved this self-reference, but Cantor&#39;s &#39;everything-in-the-fetish-book-twice&#39; parties finally sunk the idea.'),
(469, 'improvised.png', 'Improvised', 'Oh, your brother is Luke.  Sorry, should&#39;ve mentioned that first.'),
(470, 'the_end_is_not_for_a_while.png', 'The End is Not for a While', 'I THINK EVERYONE INVOLVED HERE IS CUTE.'),
(471, 'aversion_fads.png', 'Aversion Fads', 'Hey, are you friends with any hamsters?  This kite needs a passenger.'),
(472, 'house_of_pancakes.png', '&lt;span style=&quot;color: #0000ED&quot;&gt;House&lt;/span&gt; of Pancakes', 'Fuck it.  I&#39;m just going to Waffle House.'),
(473, 'still_raw.png', 'Still Raw', 'We actually divorced once over the airplane/treadmill argument.  (Preemptive response to the inevitable threads arguing about it:  you&#39;re all wrong on the internet.)'),
(474, 'turn-on.png', 'Turn-On', 'Supercollider?  I &#39;ardly know &#39;er!'),
(475, 'further_boomerang_difficulties.png', 'Further Boomerang Difficulties', 'An eternity later, the universe having turned out to have positive curvature and lots of mass, the boomerang hits him in the back of the head.'),
(476, 'one-sided.png', 'One-Sided', 'He continued, &#39;Okay, Bernanke is uncontaminated.  Find a crossbow and get him into position behind one of the columns at the Fed entrance.  This is gonna get ugly.&#39;'),
(477, 'typewriter.png', 'Typewriter', 'Somewhere in the world, my actual grandmothers are reading this and angrily exclaiming that I never write even malformed thank-you notes.  DEAR GRANDMOMS: I AM SORRY! YOU ARE WONDERFUL PEOPLE AND THANK YOU FOR EVERYTHING.  LOVE reddit.com RANDALL.'),
(478, 'the_staple_madness.png', 'The Staple Madness', 'Staple guns: because duct tape can&#39;t make that &#39;kaCHUNK&#39; noise.'),
(479, 'tones.png', 'Tones', 'I need a lawn, so I can yell at kids to stay off it.'),
(480, 'spore.png', 'Spore', 'Way to not support the GMA 950 under OS X, Spore.  :('),
(481, 'listen_to_yourself.png', 'Listen to Yourself', 'Man, I just wanted to know how babby was formed.'),
(482, 'height.png', 'Height', 'Interestingly, on a true vertical log plot, I think the Eiffel Tower&#39;s sides really would be straight lines.'),
(483, 'fiction_rule_of_thumb.png', 'Fiction Rule of Thumb', 'Except for anything by Lewis Carroll or Tolkien, you get five made-up words per story.  I&#39;m looking at you, Anathem.'),
(484, 'flash_games.png', 'Flash Games', 'Although ... who else can&#39;t wait for them to incorporate that Wiimote head-tracking stuff into games?  Man, the future&#39;s gonna be *awesome*.'),
(485, 'depth.png', 'Depth', 'The Planck length is another thousand or two pixels below the comic.'),
(486, 'i_am_not_a_ninja.png', 'I am Not a Ninja', '&#39;The sad thing is that I just wanted to talk about your poor smoke-bomb techniques.&#39;'),
(487, 'numerical_sex_positions.png', 'Numerical Sex Positions', 'We didn&#39;t even get to the continued fractions!'),
(488, 'steal_this_comic.png', 'Steal This Comic', 'I spent more time trying to get an audible.com audio book playing than it took to listen to the book.  I have lost every other piece of DRM-locked music I have paid for.'),
(489, 'going_west.png', 'Going West', 'Listen, they request that you stop submitting a listing for your house labeled &#39;WHERE YOU BROKE MY HEART&#39;.'),
(490, 'morning_routine.png', 'Morning Routine', 'I had a really hard time not writing &#39;... profit!&#39;'),
(491, 'twitter.png', 'Twitter', 'If long tooltips / cut off for you / then upgrade from / Firefox 2 / Burma Shave'),
(492, 'scrabble.png', 'Scrabble', 'A veteran Scrabble player will spot the &#39;OSTRICH&#39; option.'),
(493, 'actuarial.png', 'Actuarial', 'I started to do the tables for more famous people but it got really depressing and morbid and I had to go outside.  Hat guy wins again.'),
(494, 'secretary_part_1.png', 'Secretary: Part 1', 'The blueprints for the Department of the Internet offices call for Ceiling Cat-themed sprinkler heads.'),
(495, 'secretary_part_2.png', 'Secretary: Part 2', 'That helmet won&#39;t save him.'),
(496, 'secretary_part_3.png', 'Secretary: Part 3', 'He actually installed each piece in a different car in the lot, then built a new car in the spot from the displaced pieces.  It&#39;s a confusing maneuver known as the auto-troll shuffle.'),
(497, 'secretary_part_4.png', 'Secretary: Part 4', 'It&#39;s time to draw the line.'),
(498, 'secretary_part_5.png', 'Secretary: Part 5', 'And they choose Al Gore as Internet Secretary.'),
(499, 'scantron.png', 'Scantron', 'Also, after all the warnings about filling in the bubbles completely, I spent like 30 seconds on each one.'),
(500, 'election.png', 'Election', 'Someday I&#39;ll be rich enough to hire Nate Silver to help make all my life decisions.  &#39;Should I sleep with her?&#39;  &#39;Well, I&#39;m showing a 35% chance it will end badly.&#39;'),
(501, 'faust_20.png', 'Faust 2.0', 'The only blood these contracts are signed in is from me cutting my hand trying to open the goddamn CD case.'),
(502, 'dark_flow.png', 'Dark Flow', 'The Pioneer anomaly is due to the force of my love.'),
(503, 'terminology.png', 'Terminology', 'Also, is it just me, or do Japan and New Zealand look suspiciously similar?  Has anyone seen them at a party together?'),
(504, 'legal_hacks.png', 'Legal Hacks', 'It&#39;s totally a reasonable modern analogue.  Jefferson would have been all about crypto.'),
(505, 'a_bunch_of_rocks.png', 'A Bunch of Rocks', 'I call Rule 34 on Wolfram&#39;s Rule 34.'),
(506, 'theft_of_the_magi.png', 'Theft of the Magi', 'Every Roomba needs a dueling harness.'),
(507, 'experimentation.png', 'Experimentation', 'I understand large sample sizes are key to a low standard error of the mean, but the entire sophomore class?'),
(508, 'drapes.png', 'Drapes', 'Wait, what?'),
(509, 'induced_current.png', 'Induced Current', 'The MythBusters need to tackle whether a black hole from the LHC could REALLY destroy the world.'),
(510, 'egg_drop_failure.png', 'Egg Drop Failure', 'I hear my brother Ricky won his school&#39;s egg drop by leaving the egg inside the hen.'),
(511, 'sleet.png', 'Sleet', 'I mean, I can barely hear myself complaining about Battlestar Galactica.'),
(512, 'alternate_currency.png', 'Alternate Currency', 'For the first time ever, the phrase &#39;I&#39;d like to thank everyone at 4chan for making me successful and happy&#39; is uttered.'),
(513, 'friends.png', 'Friends', 'Friends with detriments.'),
(514, 'simultaneous.png', 'Simultaneous', 'I&#39;m leaving you for your twin.  He&#39;s more mature than you by now.'),
(515, 'no_one_must_know.png', 'No One Must Know', 'Or perhaps they knew he was there, and were just trying to torment him first.'),
(516, 'wood_chips.png', 'Wood Chips', 'You didn&#39;t run a chemical analysis against the Shroud of Turin?  Man, all that work for NOTHING.'),
(517, 'marshmallow_gun.png', 'Marshmallow Gun', 'Except in reality crossing a stream of marshmallows would create a giant Bill Murray.'),
(518, 'flow_charts.png', 'Flow Charts', 'At 8 drinks, you switch the torrent from FreeBSD to Microsoft Bob.  C&#39;mon, it&#39;ll be fun!'),
(519, '11th_grade.png', '11th Grade', 'And the ten minutes striking up a conversation with that strange kid in homeroom sometimes matters more than every other part of high school combined.'),
(520, 'cuttlefish.png', 'Cuttlefish', 'Unless the CS students finish the robot revolution before you finish the cephalopod one.'),
(521, '2008_christmas_special.png', '2008 Christmas Special', '&#39;How could you possibly think typing &#39;import skynet&#39; was a good idea?&#39;'),
(522, 'google_trends.png', 'Google Trends', 'Obama has been writing Lincoln/Obama erotic fan fiction on his secret livejournal.  Excerpt:  Lincoln lay back on the bed, nude save for his trademark stovepipe hat.  &#39;Tell me,&#39; he purred seductively, as he and Obama formed a more perfect union. &#39;When you come, is it 10% ethanol?&#39;'),
(523, 'decline.png', 'Decline', '&#39;There&#39;s also a spike on the Fourier transform at the one-month mark where --&#39; &#39;You want to stop talking right now.&#39;'),
(524, 'party.png', 'Party', 'I wonder what 2008 meme will go bizarrely mainstream in 2009 like Rickrolling did 2007-2008.  I Accidentally &lt;noun&gt;?  Yo dawg?  Place your bets now!'),
(525, 'i_know_youre_listening.png', 'I Know You&#39;re Listening', 'It&#39;s basically Pascal&#39;s Wager for the paranoid prankster.'),
(526, 'converting_to_metric.png', 'Converting to Metric', 'According to River, &#39;adequate&#39; vacuuming systems drain the human body at about half a liter per second.'),
(527, 'keynote.png', 'Keynote', 'He should be better soon -- now that the Apple Store is getting rid of DRM, Cory Doctorow will get rid of his Steve Jobs voodoo doll.'),
(528, 'windows_7.png', 'Windows 7', 'Disclaimer: I have not actually tried the beta yet.  I hear it&#39;s quite pleasant and hardly Hitler-y at all.'),
(529, 'sledding_discussion.png', 'Sledding Discussion', 'If you get your hands on that one, it&#39;s the worst place to have a breaking-up conversation.'),
(530, 'im_an_idiot.png', 'I&#39;m An Idiot', 'Sadly, this is a true story.  At least I learned about the OS X &#39;say&#39; command.'),
(531, 'contingency_plan.png', 'Contingency Plan', 'Kids are genetic experiments.  We&#39;re just experimenting responsibly!'),
(532, 'piano.png', 'Piano', 'Good thing he didn&#39;t make it smaller, or it&#39;d need someone three inches tall to play it.'),
(533, 'laptop_hell.png', 'Laptop Hell', 'The xkcd.com sysadmin has a Q2010, and I can attest that it can handle a fall down several flight of concrete steps.  Relatedly, he&#39;s upset with me -- I hope he doesn&#39;t take revenge by messing with my site&#39;s contenDISREGARD THAT I SUCK COCKS'),
(534, 'genetic_algorithms.png', 'Genetic Algorithms', 'Just make sure you don&#39;t have it maximize instead of minimize.'),
(535, 'it_might_be_cool.png', 'It Might Be Cool', '&#39;And ovaries.  Man, ovaries, huh?&#39;  [awkward pause]  &#39;... faithfully.&#39;'),
(536, 'space_elevators.png', 'Space Elevators', 'If you think space elevators are good, but just too boring and practical, check out the &#39;space fountain&#39;.'),
(537, 'ducklings.png', 'Ducklings', 'DUCKLOOP&#39;D?'),
(538, 'security.png', 'Security', 'Actual actual reality: nobody cares about his secrets.  (Also, I would be hard-pressed to find that wrench for $5.)'),
(539, 'boyfriend.png', 'Boyfriend', '... okay, but because you said that, we&#39;re breaking up.'),
(540, 'base_system.png', 'Base System', 'I once got to second base with a basketball player.  She was so confused.'),
(541, 'ted_talk.png', 'TED Talk', 'The IAU ban came after the &#39;redefinition of &#39;planet&#39; to include the IAU president&#39;s mom&#39; incident.'),
(542, 'cover_up.png', 'Cover-Up', 'Man, this trick has saved me so many times.'),
(543, 'sierpinski_valentine.png', 'Sierpinski Valentine', 'Especially you mouseover-text readers.  You&#39;re the best.  &lt;3'),
(544, 'pep_talk.png', 'Pep Talk', 'Listen!  They said a team of chess players coached by someone with no understanding of basketball would never be competitive in the NBA!  Well, it turns out they&#39;re pretty perceptive.'),
(545, 'neutrality_shmeutrality.png', 'Neutrality Schmeutrality', '&#39;Hey, everyone, you can totally trust that I didn&#39;t do a word count on MY edit!&#39;'),
(546, 'music_drm.png', 'Music DRM', 'Just yesterday I bought my first non-DRM&#39;d songs (The Last Vegas, in keeping with my &#39;I only listen to things from Guitar Hero&#39; theme).'),
(547, 'simple.png', 'Simple', 'Actually, I think if all higher math professors had to write for the Simple English Wikipedia for a year, we&#39;d be in much better shape academically.'),
(548, 'kindle.png', 'Kindle', 'I&#39;m happy with my Kindle 2 so far, but if they cut off the free Wikipedia browsing, I plan to show up drunk on Jeff Bezos&#39;s lawn and refuse to leave.'),
(549, 'westleys_a_dick.png', 'Westley&#39;s a Dick', 'Inigo/Buttercup 4eva &lt;3'),
(550, 'density.png', 'Density', 'If only I had asked 4chan for ideas for what I should do to prevent this!'),
(551, 'etch-a-sketch.png', 'Etch-a-Sketch', 'Surrounded by boring mysteries.'),
(552, 'correlation.png', 'Correlation', 'Correlation doesn&#39;t imply causation, but it does waggle its eyebrows suggestively and gesture furtively while mouthing &#39;look over there&#39;.'),
(553, 'pirate_bay.png', 'Pirate Bay', 'We find you guilty of closing your torrents as soon as they finish.  Your sentence is unremovable Hungarian subtitles on everything.'),
(554, 'not_enough_work.png', 'Not Enough Work', 'It&#39;s even harder if you&#39;re an asshole who pronounces &lt;&gt; brackets.'),
(555, 'two_mirrors.png', 'Two Mirrors', 'If you actually do this, what really happens is Douglas Hofstadter appears and talks to you for eight hours about strange loops.'),
(556, 'alternative_energy_revolution.jpg', 'Alternative Energy Revolution', 'The moment their arms spun freely in our air, they were doomed -- for Man has earned his right to hold this planet against all comers, by virtue of occasionally producing someone totally batshit insane.'),
(557, 'students.png', 'Students', 'The same goes for the one where you&#39;re wrestling the Green Ranger in the swimming pool full of Crisco.  You guys all have that dream, right?  It&#39;s not just me.  Right?'),
(558, '1000_times.png', '1000 Times', 'And 0.002 dollars will NEVER equal 0.002 cents.'),
(559, 'no_pun_intended.png', 'No Pun Intended', 'Like spelling &#39;dammit&#39; correctly -- with two m&#39;s -- it&#39;s a troll that works best on the most literate.'),
(560, 'lithium_batteries.png', 'Lithium Batteries', 'I&#39;m normally a pretty frugal person, but I still compulsively buy any R/C aircraft that&#39;s less than $30.  In the last few years, this has become a problem.'),
(561, 'well.png', 'Well', 'I&#39;ll concede ergonomics anecdotally, but none of the studies of Dvorak were at all rigorous (the most-cited Navy study was overseen by Dvorak himself).  And the &#39;slow typists down&#39; thing is a myth.  Also EMACS RULES VI DROOLS WOOOOOOO!'),
(562, 'parking.png', 'Parking', 'Police reported three dozen cheerful bystanders, yet no one claims to have seen who did it.'),
(563, 'fermirotica.png', 'Fermirotica', 'I love how Google handles dimensional analysis.  Stats are ballpark and vary wildly by time of day and whether your mom is in town.'),
(564, 'crossbows.png', 'Crossbows', 'I hate being the slowest guy in the lab.'),
(565, 'security_question.png', 'Security Question', 'Let&#39;s invite him to a party and play &#39;I never&#39;.  Okay, I never hid any bodies SOUTH of Main Street. ... he&#39;s taking a drink!'),
(566, 'matrix_revisited.png', 'Matrix Revisited', 'I actually remember being entertained by both the sequels while in the theater.  They just don&#39;t hold up nearly as well in later comparison.'),
(567, 'urgent_mission.png', 'Urgent Mission', 'Sure, we could stop dictators and pandemics, but we could also make the signs on every damn diagram make sense.'),
(568, 'well_2.png', 'Well 2', 'But I&#39;ve made $13.72 already today!  Ow, stop throwing pennies.'),
(569, 'borders.png', 'Borders', 'Eventually a UN is set up.  And then a lone rebel runs down the line of flags in front of it, runs back to his base, and gets a kajillion points.'),
(570, 'new_car.png', 'New Car', 'Somewhere out there is a company that has actually figured out how to enlarge penises, and it&#39;s helpless to reach potential customers.'),
