(611, 'disaster_voyeurism.png', 'Disaster Voyeurism', 'Hurricane forums are full of excited comments about central pressure and wind speed and comparisons to Camille and 1931 and 1938, with hastily-tacked-on notes about how it will be tragic if anyone dies and they hope it&#39;s a dud.'),
(612, 'estimation.png', 'Estimation', 'They could say &quot;the connection is probably lost,&quot; but it&#39;s more fun to do naive time-averaging to give you hope that if you wait around for 1,163 hours, it will finally finish.'),
