(730, 'circuit_diagram.png', 'Circuit Diagram', 'I just caught myself idly trying to work out what that resistor mass would actually be, and realized I had self-nerd-sniped.'),
(731, 'desert_island.png', 'Desert Island', 'Telescopes and bathyscaphes and sonar probes of Scottish lakes, Tacoma Narrows bridge collapse explained with abstract phase-space maps, some x-ray slides, a music score, Minard&#39;s Napoleonic war: the most exciting new frontier is charting what&#39;s already here.'),
(732, 'hdtv.png', 'HDTV', 'We&#39;re also stuck with blurry, juddery, slow-panning 24fps movies forever because (thanks to 60fps home video) people associate high framerates with camcorders and cheap sitcoms, and thus think good framerates look &#39;fake&#39;.');
INSERT INTO `comix` (`id`, `picid`, `title`, `alttext`) VALUES
(733, 'eagle.png', 'Eagle', 'In the off-seasons, I hire an animal trainer to help confront secret agents with situations which they are unable to report by radio.'),
(734, 'outbreak.png', 'Outbreak', 'Let&#39;s get dinner after we promptly destroy all the X-7 we&#39;ve manufactured.'),
(735, 'floor.png', 'Floor', 'We once got grounded when we convinced the FAA to block flights through our county because of ash clouds.'),
(736, 'cemetery.png', 'Cemetery', 'Three headstones down, I got a call from my mom and it went from bad to worse.'),
(737, 'yogurt.png', 'Yogurt', 'I am firmly of the opinion that if something doesn&#39;t have a year on it, every time the expiration date rolls around it is good again for the two weeks preceding that date.'),
(738, 'incision.png', 'Incision', 'At one point, by force of childhood habit, the doctor accidentally removed three or four organs.'),
(739, 'malamanteau.png', 'Malamanteau', 'The article has twenty-three citations, one of which is an obscure manuscript from the 1490&#39;s and the other twenty-two are arguments on LanguageLog.'),
(740, 'the_tell_tale_beat.png', 'The Tell-Tale Beat', 'You fancy me mad. Could a madman have outsmarted the greatest electronica/techno artists of our era? Next to fall will be Roderick Usher&#39;s house/trance band.'),
(741, 'blogging.png', 'Blogging', 'I&#39;m looking to virally monetize your eyeballs by selling them for transplants.'),
(742, 'campfire.png', 'Campfire', '100 years later, this story remains terrifying--not because it&#39;s the local network block, but because the killer is still on IPv4.'),
(743, 'infrastructures.png', 'Infrastructures', 'The heartfelt tune it plays is CC licensed, and you can get it from my seed on JoinDiaspora.com whenever that project gets going.'),
(744, 'walkthrough.png', 'Walkthrough', 'There&#39;s nothing hotter than porn dubbed over with a poorly-mic&#39;d teenager&#39;s voice explaining each step in a droning monotone. &#39;okay, we&#39;re almost at the spawn point ... separate the labia, but watch out, there are more inside them ...&quot;'),
(745, 'dyslexics.png', 'Dyslexics', 'And of course I had to redo this like three times because I kept writing &#39;UNTIE&#39;; I kept doing &#39;doing &#39;doing it wrong&#39; wrong&#39; wrong.'),
(746, 'birth.png', 'Birth', 'All those GTA marathons during the pregnancy were a bad idea.'),
(747, 'geeks_and_nerds.png', 'Geeks and Nerds', 'The definitions I grew up with were that a geek is someone unusually into something (so you could have computer geeks, baseball geeks, theater geeks, etc) and nerds are (often awkward) science, math, or computer geeks. But definitions vary.'),
(748, 'worst_case_scenario.png', 'Worst-Case Scenario', 'To get serious analyses of hurricanes and oil slicks, see Jeff Masters&#39; blog. To get serious discussions of worst-case scenario thinking, see Bruce Schneier&#39;s blog. To get enough Vitamin D, don&#39;t read any blogs and go outside instead.'),
(749, 'study.png', 'Study', 'Volunteers needed for a study on transmission of urushiol from digital contact with thin strips of fibrous cellulose pulp.'),
(750, 'book_burning.png', 'Book Burning', 'Of course, since their cautionary tale was reported in a print newspaper, no one read it.'),
(751, 'swimsuit_issue.png', 'Swimsuit Issue', 'Parents: talk to your kids about popup blockers. Also, at some point, sex. But crucial fundamentals first!'),
(752, 'phobia.png', 'Phobia', 'Oh God, the tornado picked up snakes!'),
(753, 'southern_half.png', 'Southern Half', 'Also, if you read his speech at Rice, all his arguments for going to the moon work equally well as arguments for blowing up the moon, sending cloned dinosaurs into space, or constructing a towering penis-shaped obelisk on Mars.'),
(754, 'dependencies.png', 'Dependencies', 'The prereqs for CPSC 357, the class on package management, are CPSC 432, CPSC 357, and glibc2.5 or later.'),
(755, 'interdisciplinary.png', 'Interdisciplinary', 'Replace the pendulums with history students and you&#39;ll qualify for a grant!'),
(756, 'public_opinion.png', 'Public Opinion', 'News networks giving a greater voice to viewers because the social web is so popular are like a chef on the Titanic who, seeing the looming iceberg and fleeing customers, figures ice is the future and starts making snow cones.'),
(757, 'toot.png', 'Toot', 'This is also one of only five identified situations in which a vuvuzela is actually appropriate.'),
(758, 'raptor_fences.png', 'Raptor Fences', 'If at least one person has a nightmare about being swarmed by hundreds of mouse-sized dromaeosaurids, my work will have been done.'),
(759, '3x9.png', '3x9', 'Handy exam trick: when you know the answer but not the correct derivation, derive blindly forward from the givens and backward from the answer, and join the chains once the equations start looking similar. Sometimes the graders don&#39;t notice the seam.'),
(760, 'moria.png', 'Moria', 'Someone should really bring them a ladder and remind them to build the Endless Stair *first* next time.'),
(761, 'dfs.png', 'DFS', 'A breadth-first search makes a lot of sense for dating in general, actually; it suggests dating a bunch of people casually before getting serious, rather than having a series of five-year relationships one after the other.'),
(762, 'analogies.png', 'Analogies', 'I just call all of them &#39;synecdoche&#39;.'),
(763, 'workaround.png', 'Workaround', 'I once worked on a friend&#39;s dad&#39;s computer. He had the hard drive divided into six partitions, C: through J:, with a &#39;Documents&#39; directory tree on each one. Each new file appeared to be saved to a partition at random. I knew enough not to ask.'),
(764, 'one_two.png', 'One Two', 'Cue letters from anthropology majors complaining that this view of numerolinguistic development perpetuates a widespread myth. They get to write letters like that because when you&#39;re not getting a real science degree you have a lot of free time. Zing!'),
(765, 'dilution.png', 'Dilution', 'Dear editors of Homeopathy Monthly: I have two small corrections for your July issue.  One, it&#39;s spelled &quot;echinacea&quot;, and two, homeopathic medicines are no better than placebos and your entire magazine is a sham.'),
(766, 'green_flash.png', 'Green Flash', 'The exact cause of the phenomenon is unknown, but it&#39;s thought to be linked to atmospheric refraction and you getting a really cool car.'),
(767, 'temper.png', 'Temper', 'Mr. Rogers projected an air of genuine, unwavering, almost saintly pure-hearted decency. But when you look deeper, at the person behind the image ... that&#39;s exactly what you find there, too. He&#39;s exactly what he appears to be.'),
(768, '1996.png', '1996', 'College Board issues aside, I have fond memories of TI-BASIC, writing in it a 3D graphing engine and a stock market analyzer. With enough patience, I could make anything ... but friends. (Although with my chatterbot experiments, I certainly tried.)'),
(769, 'war.png', 'War', 'They offered to make me a green beret, but I liked my regular one. Although it gets kind of squashed under my helmet.'),
(770, 'all_the_girls.png', 'All the Girls', 'You know that I&#39;ll never leave you. Not as long as she&#39;s with someone.'),
(771, 'period_speech.png', 'Period Speech', 'The same people who spend their weekends at the Blogger Reenactment Festivals will whine about the anachronisms in historical movies, but no one else will care.'),
(772, 'frogger.png', 'Frogger', 'I understand you and your team worked hard on this, but when we said to make it more realistic, we meant the graphics.'),
(773, 'university_website.png', 'University Website', 'People go to the website because they can&#39;t wait for the next alumni magazine, right? What do you mean, you want a campus map? One of our students made one as a CS class project back in &#39;01!  You can click to zoom and everything!'),
(774, 'atheists.png', 'Atheists', '&#39;But you&#39;re using that same tactic to try to feel superior to me, too!&#39; &#39;Sorry, that accusation expires after one use per conversation.&#39;'),
(775, 'savannah_ancestry.png', 'Savannah Ancestry', 'She&#39;s a perfectly nice lady from a beautiful city, and there&#39;s no reason to be mean just because she thinks a quarterback is a river in Egypt.'),
(776, 'still_no_sleep.png', 'Still No Sleep', 'I&#39;m not listening to you.  I mean, what does a SQUIRREL know about mental health?'),
(777, 'pore_strips.png', 'Pore Strips', 'I&#39;m sure they&#39;re a harmful tool of the cosmetics-industrial complex and all, but my goodness do those strips ever work to pull gunk out of your pores. I was shocked, disgusted, and vaguely fascinated by the result.'),
(778, 'scheduling.png', 'Scheduling', '&#39;How about a little ... *family growth*?&#39;  &#39;Dude, that&#39;s not until round two.&#39;'),
(779, 'anxiety.png', 'Anxiety', 'Don&#39;t need any, thanks. I have a backscattering fetish.'),
(780, 'sample.png', 'Sample', 'There are two or three songs out there with beeps in the chorus that sound exactly like the clock radio alarm I had in high school, and hearing it makes me think my life since junior year has been a dream I&#39;m about to wake up from.'),
(781, 'ahead_stop.png', 'Ahead Stop', 'They actually started the reversed-text practice in 1977 -- not for ease-of-reading reasons, but because too many people were driving backward down the highway blasting the Star Wars opening theme.'),
(782, 'desecration.png', 'Desecration', 'It gets worse! You know that wizened old monk with the gypsy wife whose voodoo shop we smash up every day after school?'),
(783, 'i_dont_want_directions.png', 'I Don&#39;t Want Directions', 'Yes, I understand that the turn is half a mile past the big field, but my GPS knows that, too.  This would be easier if you weren&#39;t about to ask me to repeat it all back to you.'),
(784, 'falling_asleep.png', 'Falling Asleep', 'Sweet unintersecting dreams!'),
(785, 'open_mic_night.png', 'Open Mic Night', 'Ever notice how the more successful observational comics become, the more their jokes focus on flying and hotels?'),
(786, 'exoplanets.png', 'Exoplanets', 'I&#39;m just worried that we&#39;ll all leave and you won&#39;t get to come along!'),
(787, 'orbiter.png', 'Orbiter', 'Normally, the Shuttle can&#39;t quite safely reach the orbital inclination required to pass over both those points from a Canaveral launch, but this is an alternate history in which either it launches from Vandenberg or everyone hates the Outer Banks.'),
(788, 'the_carriage.png', 'The Carriage', 'I learned from Achewood that since this poem is in ballad meter, it can be sung to the tune of Gilligan&#39;s Island.  Since then, try as I might, I haven&#39;t ONCE been able to read it normally.'),
(789, 'showdown.png', 'Showdown', 'The tumbleweed then tried to roll off into the sunset, but due to the Old West&#39;s placement north of the subtropical ridge, the prevailing winds were in the wrong direction.'),
(790, 'control.png', 'Control', 'Which, at one point, led to a study showing that LSD produces no more hallucinations than a placebo.'),
(791, 'leaving.png', 'Leaving', 'What&#39;ll I say -- &quot;I was staring at some cat vomit when I got the news?&quot;'),
(792, 'password_reuse.png', 'Password Reuse', 'It&#39;ll be hilarious the first few times this happens.'),
(793, 'physicists.png', 'Physicists', 'If you need some help with the math, let me know, but that should be enough to get you started! Huh? No, I don&#39;t need to read your thesis, I can imagine roughly what it says.'),
(794, 'inside_joke.png', 'Inside Joke', 'I&#39;ve looked through a few annotated versions of classic books, and it&#39;s shocking how much of what&#39;s in there is basically pop-culture references totally lost on us now.'),
(795, 'conditional_risk.png', 'Conditional Risk', '&#39;Dude, wait -- I&#39;m not American! So my risk is basically zero!&#39;'),
(796, 'bad_ex.png', 'Bad Ex', 'Since the goatee, glasses, and Seltzer &amp; Friedberg DVD collection didn&#39;t tip you off, there will be a $20 negligence charge for this service.'),
(797, 'debian_main.png', 'debian-main', 'dpkg: error processing package (--purge): subprocess pre-removal script returned error exit 163: OH_GOD_THEYRE_INSIDE_MY_CLOTHES'),
(798, 'adjectives.png', 'Adjectives', '&#39;Fucking ineffable&#39; sounds like someone remembering how to do self-censorship halfway through a phrase.'),
(799, 'stephen_hawking.png', 'Stephen Hawking', '&#39;Guys?  The Town is supposed to be good, and I thou--&#39; &#39;PHYSICIST STEPHEN HAWKING DECLARES NEW FILM BEST IN ALL SPACE AND TIME&#39; &#39;No, I just heard that--&#39; &#39;SHOULD SCIENCE PLAY A ROLE IN JUDGING BEN AFFLECK?&#39; &#39;I don&#39;t think--&#39; &#39;WHAT ABOUT MATT DAMON?&#39;'),
(800, 'beautiful_dream.png', 'Beautiful Dream', 'Lucky. In MY dream, all the people who grew up loving The Giving Tree paired up with all the students who had weird dreams after reading The Metamorphosis. That one was more confusing.'),
(801, 'golden_hammer.png', 'Golden Hammer', 'Took me five tries to find the right one, but I managed to salvage our night out--if not the boat--in the end.'),
(802, 'online_communities_2.png', 'Online Communities 2', 'Best trivia I learned while working on this: &#39;Man, Farmville is so huge! Do you realize it&#39;s the second-biggest browser-based social-networking-centered farming game in the WORLD?&#39; Then you wait for the listener to do a double-take.'),
(803, 'airfoil.png', 'Airfoil', 'This is a fun explanation to prepare your kids for; it&#39;s common and totally wrong. Good lines include &#39;why does the air have to travel on both sides at the same time?&#39; and &#39;I saw the Wright brothers plane and those wings were curved the same on the top and bottom!&#39;'),
(804, 'pumpkin_carving.png', 'Pumpkin Carving', 'The Banach-Tarski theorem was actually first developed by King Solomon, but his gruesome attempts to apply it set back set theory for centuries.'),
(805, 'paradise_city.png', 'Paradise City', 'Take me down to the paradise municipality / where the grass is mauve and the girls aren&#39;t fromthisreality.'),
(806, 'tech_support.png', 'Tech Support', 'I recently had someone ask me to go get a computer and turn it on so I could restart it. He refused to move further in the script until I said I had done that.'),
(807, 'connected.png', 'Connected', 'Or love in general, for that matter. It just leads to the idea that either your love is pure, perfect, and eternal, and you are storybook-compatible in every way with no problems, or you&#39;re LYING when you say &#39;I love you&#39;.'),
(808, 'the_economic_argument.png', 'The Economic Argument', 'Not to be confused with &#39;making money selling this stuff to OTHER people who think it works&#39;, which corporate accountants and actuaries have zero problems with.'),
(809, 'los_alamos.png', 'Los Alamos', 'The test didn&#39;t (spoiler alert) destroy the world, but the fact that they were even doing those calculations makes theirs the coolest jobs ever.'),
(810, 'constructive.png', 'Constructive', 'And what about all the people who won&#39;t be able to join the community because they&#39;re terrible at making helpful and constructive co-- ... oh.'),
(811, 'starlight.png', 'Starlight', 'Don&#39;t worry! From the light&#39;s point of view, home and your eye are in the same place, and the journey takes no time at all! Relativity saves the day again.'),
(812, 'glass.png', 'Glass', 'I read in this one article that the breaking of electroweak symmetry is the reason we have SOULS. This guy with a degree said so!'),
(813, 'one_liners.png', 'One-Liners', '&#39;Upgrade to the latest version of Adobe Flash player to view THIS content, bitch.&#39; ::triggers detonator::'),
(814, 'diode.png', 'Diode', 'And the worst part is you won&#39;t apologize.'),
(815, 'mu.png', 'Mu', 'As the CoKF approaches 0, productivity goes negative as you pull OTHER people into chair-spinning contests.'),
(816, 'applied_math.png', 'Applied Math', 'Dear Reader: Enclosed is a check for ninety-eight cents. Using your work, I have proven that this equals the amount you requested.'),
(817, 'mutual.png', 'Mutual', 'A universe that needed someone to observe it in order to collapse it into existence would be a pretty sorry universe indeed.'),
(818, 'illness.png', 'Illness', '&lt;3 If there&#39;s anything you can do, I&#39;ll let you know. For the moment, any simple distracting online games sent to sick@xkcd.com will not go unappreciated [EDIT: Holy crap 2,700 games before noon. I love you guys; thank you. They will be passed along and played by us all.]'),
(819, 'five_minute_comics_part_1.png', 'Five-Minute Comics: Part 1', 'The wolves thin the RAID arrays, removing the slowest and weakest disks to keep the average seek speed high.'),
(820, 'five_minute_comics_part_2.png', 'Five-Minute Comics: Part 2', 'Dear Wiccan readers: I understand modern Wiccans are not usually all about the curses and hexes. But Darth Vader was recently converted from Episcopalianism and he&#39;s still figuring it all out.'),
(821, 'five_minute_comics_part_3.png', 'Five-Minute Comics: Part 3', 'Resulting in The Little Rock 9x + C.'),
(822, 'guest_week_jeph_jacques_questionable_content.png', 'Guest Week: Jeph Jacques (Questionable Content)', 'Guest comic by Jeph Jacques of Questionable Content, whose internal monologue hasn&#39;t been speaking to him for the past three years.'),
(823, 'guest_week_david_troupes_buttercup_festival.png', 'Guest Week: David Troupes (Buttercup Festival)', 'Guest comic by David Troupes of Buttercup Festival, who is living in that lovely tree outside your window.'),
(824, 'guest_week_bill_amend_foxtrot.png', 'Guest Week: Bill Amend (FoxTrot)', 'Guest comic by Bill Amend of FoxTrot, an inspiration to all us nerdy-physics-majors-turned-cartoonists, of which there are an oddly large number.'),
(825, 'guest_week_jeffrey_rowland_overcompensating.png', 'Guest Week: Jeffrey Rowland (Overcompensating)', 'Guest comic by Jeffrey Rowland of Overcompensating/Wigu.  Jeffrey is famous as the picture on the Wikipedia article on &#39;Necrosis&#39;.'),
(826, 'guest_week_zach_weiner_smbc.png', 'Guest Week: Zach Weiner (SMBC)', 'Guest comic by Zach Weiner of Saturday Morning Breakfast Cereal. When I was stressed out, Zach gave me a talk that was really encouraging and somehow involved nanobots.'),
(827, 'business_idea.png', 'Business Idea', 'We didn&#39;t believe you at first, but we asked like three people who were at that party. They not only corroborated your story, but even said you totally mentioned wanting to start a company someday. Sorry! If this isn&#39;t enough money, let us know.'),
(828, 'positive_attitude.png', 'Positive Attitude', 'Having a positive attitude is almost tautologically good for your mental health, and extreme stress can hurt your immune system, but that doesn&#39;t mean you should feel like shit for feeling like shit.'),
(829, 'arsenic_based_life.png', 'Arsenic-Based Life', 'According to a new paper published in the journal Science, reporters are unable to thrive in an arsenic-rich environment.'),
(830, 'genetic_analysis.png', 'Genetic Analysis', 'There&#39;s still a chance you were conceived via IVF. But we&#39;ve checked your mom&#39;s college yearbook photos, and whether or not she and your father had sex, it&#39;s clear that ... listen, I know this is hard for you.'),
(831, 'weather_radar.png', 'Weather Radar', 'Ever notice how there aren&#39;t as many thunderstorms now as there were when you were a kid?  Much like &#39;the shuffle on my MP3 player has a bias&#39;, this is occasionally true but universally believed. Brains are so interesting!'),
(832, 'tic_tac_toe.png', 'Tic-Tac-Toe', 'The only winning move is to play, perfectly, waiting for your opponent to make a mistake.'),
(833, 'convincing.png', 'Convincing', 'And if you labeled your axes, I could tell you exactly how MUCH better.'),
(834, 'wikileaks.png', 'Wikileaks', 'STUDENTS ARE CALLING PRESIDENT JOHNSON EN MASSE TO PROTEST THE BOMBING AND IT&#39;S JAMMED THE WHITE HOUSE SWITCHBOARD. COULD THEY COLLAPSE OUR CRITICAL PHONE SYSTEMS? HAS THE FIRST TELEPHONE WAR BEGUN? STAY TUNED FOR MORE ON THIS DANGEROUS NEW TECHNOLOGY.'),
(835, 'tree.png', 'Tree', 'Not only is that terrible in general, but you just KNOW Billy&#39;s going to open the root present first, and then everyone will have to wait while the heap is rebuilt.'),
(836, 'sickness.png', 'Sickness', 'At least, with p&lt;0.05 confidence.'),
(837, 'coupon_code.png', 'Coupon Code', 'This also guarantees he won&#39;t be one of the ones to get a bobcat.'),
(838, 'incident.png', 'Incident', 'He sees you when you&#39;re sleeping, he knows when you&#39;re awake, he&#39;s copied on /var/spool/mail/root, so be good for goodness&#39; sake.'),
(839, 'explorers.png', 'Explorers', 'We&#39;re going to have to work together to get over our hangups if we&#39;re going to learn to move on Catan&#39;s hexagonal grid. It&#39;s bad enough that we lost our crew of pawns when we passed within firing range of Battleship.'),
(840, 'serious.png', 'Serious', 'Not to be confused with Serious PuTTY, the Windows terminal client where everything is in Impact.'),
(841, 'audiophiles.png', 'Audiophiles', 'For years, I took the wrong lesson from that Monster Cable experiment and only listened to my music through alligator-clipped coat hangers.'),
(842, 'mark.png', 'Mark', 'I&#39;m a solipsistic conspiracy theorist. I&#39;m sure I must be up to something, and I will not stop until I find out what.'),
(843, 'misconceptions.png', 'Misconceptions', '&#39;Grandpa, what was it like in the Before time?&#39; &#39;It was hell. People went around saying glass was a slow-flowing liquid. You folks these days don&#39;t know how good you have it.&#39;'),
(844, 'good_code.png', 'Good Code', 'You can either hang out in the Android Loop or the HURD loop.'),
(845, 'modern_history.png', 'Modern History', 'During the week, I research my character by living in his house and raising his children.'),
(846, 'dental_nerve.png', 'Dental Nerve', 'WAKE up in the MORning and my BREATH ain&#39;t PREtty / and noBODY&#39;S gonna KISS me if my MOUTH smells SHItty / so I ALways brush my TEETH before I START on the JACK / sure, my DRINKing&#39;s out of HAND, but I&#39;m conTROLLing my PLAQUE.'),
(847, 'stingray_nebula.png', 'Stingray Nebula', 'EÃ¤rendil will patrol the walls of night only until the sun reaches red giant stage, engulfing the Morning Star on his brow. Light and high beauty are passing things as well.'),
(848, '3d.png', '3D', 'The LINACs in the glasses frames can barely manage one MeV. You should&#39;ve gone to the screening at CERN.'),
(849, 'complex_conjugate.png', 'Complex Conjugate', 'Fun fact: if you say this every time a professor does something to a complex-number equation that drops the imaginary part, they&#39;ll eventually move the class to another room and tell everyone else except you.'),
(850, 'world_according_to_americans.png', 'World According to Americans', 'It&#39;s not our fault we caught a group on their way home from a geography bee. And they taught us that Uzbekistan is one of the world&#39;s two doubly-landlocked countries!'),
(851, 'na.png', 'Na', 'I hear that there are actual lyrics later on in Land of 1,000 Dances, but other than the occasional &#39;I said,&#39; I&#39;ve never listened long enough to hear any of them.'),
(852, 'local_g.png', 'Local g', 'In Rio de Janeiro in 2016, the same jump will get an athlete 0.25% higher (&gt;1cm) than in London four years prior.'),
(853, 'consecutive_vowels.png', 'Consecutive Vowels', 'But the windows! What if there&#39;s a voyeur watchi-- wait, now I&#39;m turned on too.'),
(854, 'learning_to_cook.png', 'Learning to Cook', 'And yet I never stop thinking, &#39;sure, these ingredients cost more than a restaurant meal, but think how many meals I&#39;ll get out of them! Especially since each one will have leftovers!&#39;'),
(855, '1999.png', '1999', '&#39;Whoa, twenty-two in two hours!&#39; &#39;Your site got twenty-two hundred hits in two hours?&#39; &#39;No. Twenty-two. But still, that&#39;s like half the people on the internet!&#39;'),
(856, 'trochee_fixation.png', 'Trochee Fixation', 'If you Huffman-coded all the &#39;random&#39; things everyone on the internet has said over the years, you&#39;d wind up with, like, 30 or 40 bytes *tops*.'),
(857, 'archimedes.png', 'Archimedes', 'Give a man a fish, or he will destroy the only existing vial of antidote.'),
(858, 'milk.png', 'Milk', 'It&#39;s not hard when you have the same thought like 40 or 50 percent of the time.'),
(859, '(.png', '(', 'Brains aside, I wonder how many poorly-written xkcd.com-parsing scripts will break on this title (or ;;&quot;&#39;&#39;{&lt;&lt;[&#39; this mouseover text.&quot;'),
(860, 'never_do_this.png', 'Never Do This', 'I call Rule 34 on The Secret House.'),
(861, 'wisdom_teeth.png', 'Wisdom Teeth', 'I heard the general anesthesia drugs can cause amnesia, so when I woke up mid-extraction I started taking notes on my hand so I&#39;d remember things later. I managed &#39;AWAKE BUT EVERYTHING OK&#39; before the dental assistant managed to find and confiscate all my pens.'),
(862, 'let_go.png', 'Let Go', 'After years of trying various methods, I broke this habit by pitting my impatience against my laziness. I decoupled the action and the neurological reward by setting up a simple 30-second delay I had to wait through, in which I couldn&#39;t do anything else, before any new page or chat client would load (and only allowed one to run at once). The urge to check all those sites magically vanished--and my &#39;productive&#39; computer use was unaffected.'),
(863, 'major_in_the_universe.png', 'Major in the Universe', 'I hear Steven Levitt is writing a book analyzing A.J. Jacobs&#39; quest to spend a year reading everything Malcolm Gladwell ever wrote. The audiobook will be narrated by Robert Krulwich of Radiolab.'),
(864, 'flying_cars.png', 'Flying Cars', 'It&#39;s hard to fit in the backseat of my flying car with my android Realdoll when we&#39;re both wearing jetpacks.'),
(865, 'nanobots.png', 'Nanobots', 'I think the IETF hit the right balance with the 128 bits thing. We can fit MAC addresses in a /64 subnet, and the nanobots will only be able to devour half the planet.'),
(866, 'compass_and_straightedge.png', 'Compass and Straightedge', 'The Greeks long suspected this, but it wasn&#39;t until April 12th of 1882 that Ferdinand von Lindemann conclusively proved it when he constructed himself the most awesome birthday party possible and nobody showed up.'),
(867, 'herpetology.png', 'Herpetology', 'Birds are Aves, which is part of the clade Theropoda, which is in Saurischia, which is in Dinosauria. Those birds outside our windows are dinosaurs. We can clear out the rest of our brains because we now have the best fact.'),
(868, 'nolan_chart.png', 'Nolan Chart', 'Also in the right quadrant are NFPA-compliant chemical manufacturers and Sir Charles Wheatstone. Sharing the top with the internet libertarians are Nate Silver and several politically-active kite designers.'),
(869, 'server_attention_span.png', 'Server Attention Span', 'They have to keep the adjacent rack units empty. Otherwise, half the entries in their /var/log/syslog are just &#39;SERVER BELOW TRYING TO START CONVERSATION *AGAIN*.&#39; and &#39;WISH THEY&#39;D STOP GIVING HIM SO MUCH COFFEE IT SPLATTERS EVERYWHERE.&#39;'),
(870, 'mathematically_annoying.png', 'Advertising', 'I remember the exact moment in my childhood when I realized, while reading a flyer, that nobody would ever spend money solely to tell me they wanted to give me something for nothing. It&#39;s a much more vivid memory than the (related) parental Santa talk.'),
(871, 'charity.png', 'Charity', 'I usually respond to someone else doing something good by figuring out a reason that they&#39;re not really as good as they seem. But I&#39;ve been realizing lately that there&#39;s an easier way to handle these situations, and it involves zero internet arguments.'),
(872, 'fairy_tales.png', 'Fairy Tales', 'Goldilocks&#39; discovery of Newton&#39;s method for approximation required surprisingly few changes.'),
(873, 'fps_mod.png', 'FPS Mod', 'Wait, that second one is a woman?  ... wait, if that bothers me, then why doesn&#39;t ... man, this game is no fun anymore.'),
(874, 'time_management.png', 'Time Management', 'I never trust anyone who&#39;s more excited about success than about doing the thing they want to be successful at.'),
(875, '2009_called.png', '2009 Called', '2017 called, but I couldn&#39;t understand what they were saying over all the screams.'),
(876, 'trapped.png', 'Trapped', 'Socrates could&#39;ve saved himself a lot of trouble if he&#39;d just brought a flashlight, tranquilizer gun, and a bunch of rescue harnesses.'),
(877, 'beauty.png', 'Beauty', 'The best hugs are probably from hagfish, which can extrude microscopic filaments that convert a huge volume of water around them to slime in seconds. Instant cozy blanket!'),
(878, 'model_rail.png', 'Model Rail', 'I don&#39;t know what&#39;s more telling--the number of pages in the Wikipedia talk page argument over whether the 1/87.0857143 scale is called &quot;HO&quot; or &quot;H0&quot;, or the fact that within minutes of first hearing of it I had developed an extremely strong opinion on the issue.'),
(879, 'lamp.png', 'Lamp', '&#39;That was definitely not in my top three wishes.&#39; &#39;Who said anything about YOUR wishes?&#39;'),
(880, 'headache.png', 'Headache', 'I&#39;m only willing to visit placid lakes, salt flats, and painting exhibits until the world&#39;s 3D technology improves.'),
(881, 'probability.png', 'Probability', 'My normal approach is useless here, too.'),
(882, 'significant.png', 'Significant', '&#39;So, uh, we did the green study again and got no link. It was probably a--&#39; &#39;RESEARCH CONFLICTED ON GREEN JELLY BEAN/ACNE LINK; MORE STUDY RECOMMENDED!&#39;'),
(883, 'pain_rating.png', 'Pain Rating', 'If it were a two or above I wouldn&#39;t be able to answer because it would mean a pause in the screaming.'),
(884, 'rogers_st.png', 'Rogers St.', '&#39;We can also use middle names in place of first pet&#39;s names, but yours is something incomprehensible about dropping tables.&#39;'),
(885, 'recycling.png', 'Recycling', 'And given how much of my stuff they go through, they definitely know where I live.'),
(886, 'craigslist_apartments.png', 'Craigslist Apartments', '$1600 / 1386153BR 3BATH, MODERN SLIDING DOORS, GUEST ROOMS, GARBAGE DISPOSAL. FREE MANDATORY PARKING (ENFORCED). CONVENIENT TO ALDERAAN.'),
(887, 'future_timeline.png', 'Future Timeline', 'Not shown: the approximately 30,000 identical, vaguely hysterical articles titled &quot;WHITE PEOPLE IN [THE US/BRITAIN] TO BECOME MINORITY BY [YEAR]!&quot;, which came up for basically any year I put in.'),
(888, 'heaven.png', 'Heaven', 'If you&#39;ve never had sex, this is what it feels like. Complete with the brief feeling of satisfaction, followed by ennui, followed by getting bored and trying to make it happen again.'),
(889, 'turtles.png', 'Turtles', 'You&#39;re a turtle!'),
(890, 'etymology.png', 'Etymology', 'For some reason, my childhood suspension of disbelief had no problem with the fact that this ancient galaxy is full of humans, but was derailed by language. There&#39;s no Asia OR Europe there, so where&#39;d they get all the Indo-European roots?'),
(891, 'movie_ages.png', 'Movie Ages', 'If you&#39;re 15 or younger, then just remember that it&#39;s nevertheless probably too late to be a child prodigy.'),
(892, 'null_hypothesis.png', 'Null Hypothesis', 'Hell, my eighth grade science class managed to conclusively reject it just based on a classroom experiment. It&#39;s pretty sad to hear about million-dollar research teams who can&#39;t even manage that.'),
(893, '65_years.png', '65 Years', 'The universe is probably littered with the one-planet graves of cultures which made the sensible economic decision that there&#39;s no good reason to go into space--each discovered, studied, and remembered by the ones who made the irrational decision.'),
(894, 'progeny.png', 'Progeny', 'I tell my children &#39;it&#39;s not whether you win or lose, it&#39;s how you play the game.&#39; I&#39;m trying to take the edge off their competitive drive to ensure that I can always beat them.'),
(895, 'teaching_physics.png', 'Teaching Physics', 'Space-time is like some simple and familiar system which is both intuitively understandable and precisely analogous, and if I were Richard Feynman I&#39;d be able to come up with it.'),
(896, 'marie_curie.png', 'Marie Curie', 'Although not permanently.'),
(897, 'elevator_inspection.png', 'Elevator Inspection', 'Even governmental elevator inspectors get bored halfway through asking where the building office is.'),
(898, 'chain_of_command.png', 'Chain of Command', 'Themistocles said his infant son ruled all Greece -- &quot;Athens rules all Greece; I control Athens; my wife controls me; and my infant son controls her.&quot; Thus, nowadays the world is controlled by whoever buys advertising time on Dora the Explorer.'),
(899, 'number_line.png', 'Number Line', 'The Wikipedia page &quot;List of Numbers&quot; opens with &quot;This list is incomplete; you can help by expanding it.&quot;'),
(900, 'religions.png', 'Religions', 'But to us there is but one God, plus or minus one. --1 Corinthians 8:6Â±2.'),
(901, 'temperature.png', 'Temperature', 'And the baby has a fever.'),
(902, 'darmok_and_jalad.png', 'Darmok and Jalad', 'I wonder how often Patrick Stewart has Darmok flashbacks when talking to Star Trek fans.'),
(903, 'extended_mind.png', 'Extended Mind', 'Wikipedia trivia: if you take any article, click on the first link in the article text not in parentheses or italics, and then repeat, you will eventually end up at &quot;Philosophy&quot;.'),
(904, 'sports.png', 'Sports', 'Also, all financial analysis. And, more directly, D&amp;D.'),
(905, 'homeownership.png', 'Homeownership', 'New research shows over 60% of the financial collapse&#39;s toxic assets were created by power drills.'),
(906, 'citations.png', 'Advertising Discovery', 'When advertisers figure this out, our only weapon will be blue sharpies and &quot;[disputed]&quot;.'),
(907, 'ages.png', 'Ages', 'Every age: &quot;I&#39;m glad I&#39;m not the clueless person I was five years ago, but now I don&#39;t want to get any older.&quot;'),
(908, 'the_cloud.png', 'The Cloud', 'There&#39;s planned downtime every night when we turn on the Roomba and it runs over the cord.'),
(909, 'worst_case_shopping.png', 'Worst-Case Shopping', 'Wait a minute. If I&#39;m escaping from a submarine at 50 meters, then I&#39;ll *definitely* need a flashlight to find air pockets for gradual decompression on the way up. Time to start shopping professional dive lights.'),
(910, 'permanence.png', 'Permanence', 'This hostname is going in dozens of remote config files. Changing a kid&#39;s name is comparatively easy!'),
(911, 'magic_school_bus.png', 'Magic School Bus', 'At my OLD school, we used Microsoft Encarta 2005.'),
(912, 'manual_override.png', 'Manual Override', 'I think you mean &#39;GNU Info Override&#39;.'),
(913, 'core.png', 'Core', 'If you&#39;re a geologist or geophysicist and you don&#39;t introduce yourself by saying your name, then gesturing downward and saying &quot;... and I study that&quot;, I don&#39;t know what you&#39;re doing with your life.'),
(914, 'ice.png', 'Ice', 'On the plus side, she wrote &#39;Welcome to the AAA Club!&#39; in lipstick on the bathroom mirror, and left me a membership/roadside assistance card on the counter.'),
(915, 'connoisseur.png', 'Connoisseur', 'Our brains have just one scale, and we resize our experiences to fit.'),
(916, 'unpickable.png', 'Unpickable', 'The safe is empty except for an unsolved 5x5 Rubik&#39;s cube.'),
(917, 'hofstadter.png', 'Hofstadter', '&quot;This is the reference implementation of the self-referential joke.&quot;'),
(918, 'googleplus.png', 'Google+', 'On one hand, you&#39;ll never be able to convince your parents to switch. On the other hand, you&#39;ll never be able to convince your parents to switch!'),
(919, 'tween_bromance.png', 'Tween Bromance', 'Verbiage. Va-jay-jay. Irregardless.'),
(920, 'youtube_parties.png', 'YouTube Parties', 'This reminds me of that video where ... no? How have you not seen that? Oh man, let me find it. No, it&#39;s ok, we can go back to your video later.'),
(921, 'delivery_notification.png', 'Delivery Notification', 'You can arrange a pickup of your sword in Rivendell between the hours of noon and 7:00 PM.'),
(922, 'fight_club.png', 'Fight Club', 'I&#39;m not saying it&#39;s all bad, but that movie has not aged as well as my teenage self in 2000 was confident it would.'),
(923, 'strunk_and_white.png', 'Strunk and White', 'The best thing about Strunk/White fanfiction is that it&#39;s virtually guaranteed to be well written.'),
(924, '3d_printer.png', '3D Printer', 'I just can&#39;t wait for the Better Homes and Gardens list of helpful tips for household reuse of sixteen-inch acrylonitrile-butadiene-styrene phalluses.'),
(925, 'cell_phones.png', 'Cell Phones', 'He holds the laptop like that on purpose, to make you cringe.'),
(926, 'time_vulture.png', 'Time Vulture', 'In a way, all vultures are Time Vultures; some just have more patience than others.'),
(927, 'standards.png', 'Standards', 'Fortunately, the charging one has been solved now that we&#39;ve all standardized on mini-USB. Or is it micro-USB? Shit.'),
(928, 'mimic_octopus.png', 'Mimic Octopus', 'Even if the dictionaries are starting to give in, I refuse to accept &#39;octopi&#39; as a word mainly because--I&#39;m not making this up--there&#39;s a really satisfying climactic scene in the Orson Scott Card horror novel &#39;Lost Boys&#39; which hinges on it being an incorrect pluralization.'),
(929, 'speculation.png', 'Speculation', '&#39;I was pretty good at skeet shooting, but was eventually kicked off the range for catching the clay pigeons in a net and dispatching them execution-style.&#39;'),
(930, 'days_of_the_week.png', 'Days of the Week', 'Not pictured: the elongated Halley&#39;s-Comet-like orbit of every Rebecca Black lyric.'),
(931, 'lanes.png', 'Lanes', 'Each quarter of the lanes from left to right correspond loosely to breast cancer stages one through four (at diagnosis).'),
(932, 'cia.png', 'CIA', 'It was their main recruiting poster, hung nearly ten feet up a wall! This means the hackers have LADDER technology! Are we headed for a future where everyone has to pay $50 for one of those locked plexiglass poster covers? More after the break ...'),
(933, 'tattoo.png', 'Tattoo', 'I calculate that the electrons in radiation therapy hit you at 99.8% of the speed of light, and the beam used in a 90-second gamma ray therapy session could, if fired with less precision, kill a horse (they did not let me test this).'),
(934, 'mac_pc.png', 'Mac/PC', 'It&#39;s fun to watch browsers fumblingly recapitulate the history of window management. Someday we&#39;ll have xmonad as a Firefox extension.'),
(935, 'missed_connections.png', 'Missed Connections', 'The Street View van isn&#39;t going to find out anything Google won&#39;t already know from reading my email.'),
(936, 'password_strength.png', 'Password Strength', 'To anyone who understands information theory and security and is in an infuriating argument with someone who does not (possibly involving mixed case), I sincerely apologize.'),
(937, 'tornadoguard.png', 'TornadoGuard', 'The bug report was marked &#39;could not reproduce&#39;.'),
(938, 't_cells.png', 'T-Cells', '&#39;We&#39;re not sure how to wipe out the chimeral T-cells after they&#39;ve destroyed the cancer. Though I do have this vial of smallpox ...&#39;'),
(939, 'arrow.png', 'Arrow', '&#39;The Return of the Boomerang&#39; would make a great movie title.'),
(940, 'oversight.png', 'Oversight', 'I felt so clever when I found a way to game the Fitocracy system by incorporating a set of easy but high-scoring activities into my regular schedule. Took me a bit to realize I&#39;d been tricked into setting up a daily exercise routine.'),
(941, 'depth_perception.png', 'Depth Perception', 'I&#39;ve looked at clouds from both sides now.'),
(942, 'juggling.png', 'Juggling', 'Later: &#39;Why is there a book hovering over the trash can?&#39;'),
(943, 'empirical.png', 'Empirical', 'I&#39;m as surprised as you!'),
(944, 'hurricane_names.png', 'Hurricane Names', 'After exhausting the OED, we started numbering them. When overlapping hurricanes formed at all points on the Earth&#39;s surface, and our scheme was foiled by Cantor diagonalization, we just decided to name them all &quot;Steve&quot;. Your local forecast tomorrow is &quot;Steve&quot;. Good luck.'),
(945, 'im_sorry.png', 'I&#39;m Sorry', 'You know I&#39;ve always hated her.'),
(946, 'family_decals.png', 'Family Decals', 'My decal set has no adults, just a sea of hundreds of the little girl figures closing in around a single cat.'),
(947, 'investing.png', 'Investing', 'But Einstein said it was the most powerful force in the universe, and I take all my investment advice from flippant remarks by theoretical physicists making small talk at parties.'),
(948, 'ai.png', 'AI', 'And they both react poorly to showers.'),
(949, 'file_transfer.png', 'File Transfer', 'Every time you email a file to yourself so you can pull it up on your friend&#39;s laptop, Tim Berners-Lee sheds a single tear.'),
(950, 'mystery_solved.png', 'Mystery Solved', 'The Roanoke Lost Colonists founded Roanoke, the Franklin Expedition reached the Pacific in 2009 when the Northwest Passage opened, and Jimmy Hoffa currently heads the Teamsters Union--he just started going by &#39;James&#39;.'),
(951, 'working.png', 'Working', 'And if you drive a typical car more than a mile out of your way for each penny you save on the per-gallon price, it doesn&#39;t matter how worthless your time is to you--the gas to get you there and back costs more than you save.'),
(952, 'stud_finder.png', 'Stud Finder', 'According to every stud finder I&#39;ve tried to use, my walls contain a rapidly shifting network of hundreds and hundreds of studs.'),
(953, '1_to_10.png', '1 to 10', 'If you get an 11/100 on a CS test, but you claim it should be counted as a &#39;C&#39;, they&#39;ll probably decide you deserve the upgrade.'),
(954, 'chin_up_bar.png', 'Chin-Up Bar', 'Those few who escaped found the emergency cutoff box disabled. The stampede lasted two hours and reached the bottom three times.'),
(955, 'neutrinos.png', 'Neutrinos', 'I can&#39;t speak to the paper&#39;s scientific merits, but it&#39;s really cool how on page 10 you can see that their reference GPS beacon is sensitive enough to pick up continential drift under the detector (interrupted halfway through by an earthquake).'),
(956, 'sharing.png', 'Sharing', 'In the new edition of The Giving Tree, the tree uses social tools to share with its friend all the best places to buy things.'),
(957, 'development.png', 'Development', 'Funding was quickly restored to the NHC and the APA was taken back off hurricane forecast duty.'),
